The paper deals with the analysis of wireless communication networks, specifically heterogeneous cellular networks, using stochastic geometry. This falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), communication (cs.COMM), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper introduces a new analytical methodology, which involves the computation of integrals, which could also fall under the scope of mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
